While I enjoyed this and I understand it is a different game, Samorost 3 
just didn't have a lasting impression compared to Machinarium. I didn't 
connect with the main character, I didn't understand their motivations. It 
felt like one little task after the other, aimlessly travelling and before 
you know it it's over. I remember completing the main quest and just 
feeling confused. Compared to the experience I had with Machinarium, this 
game fell short. I don't feel compelled to play it again, I've played 
Machinarium multiple times and love every minute of it. Even Botanicula 
connected me to the world unlike this joyless mess. Obviously the art style 
is beautiful and character design is great, eccept the main characters, I 
feel their bland design accounts for some of my lack of interest towards 
their goals. I'm glad I got this in the sale and didn't pay full retail.
